03:14:33.412 --> 03:14:35.456
“How you doing?
You're looking good.”

03:14:35.456 --> 03:14:37.333
Or...

03:14:39.042 --> 03:14:42.087
...”I was hoping
I'd never see you again.”

03:14:44.507 --> 03:14:49.719
I never thought I would. There's
a difference.

03:14:51.639 --> 03:14:54.057
At least you recognized me.
That's something.

03:14:54.057 --> 03:14:56.935
Actresses have good memories.

03:15:07.237 --> 03:15:09.532
You want a drink?

03:15:14.036 --> 03:15:16.121
I'm having one.

03:15:26.674 --> 03:15:28.008
Margo.

03:15:29.426 --> 03:15:30.678
Yes, miss?

03:15:30.678 --> 03:15:32.638
That's all for now.
You can go.

03:15:32.638 --> 03:15:34.598
All right, miss.

03:15:39.061 --> 03:15:41.522
She called you “miss.”

03:15:42.981 --> 03:15:45.025
You never
got married?

03:15:46.402 --> 03:15:48.028
No.

03:15:51.407 --> 03:15:52.991
You live alone?

03:16:00.957 --> 03:16:02.959
No.

03:16:09.299 --> 03:16:11.134
Where were you?

03:16:14.388 --> 03:16:16.515
I was out of town.

03:16:19.851 --> 03:16:21.978
Have you
been back long?

03:16:23.355 --> 03:16:26.149
Couple of days.

03:16:26.149 --> 03:16:28.026
You staying?

03:16:39.996 --> 03:16:41.831
That depends.

03:16:44.376 --> 03:16:46.754
Why do you wanna see me?

03:16:48.422 --> 03:16:50.966
Two reasons.

03:16:50.966 --> 03:16:54.177
First, I wanted to see
if you did the right thing

03:16:54.177 --> 03:16:56.555
turning me down
to become an actress.

03:17:00.434 --> 03:17:02.102
Well?

03:17:04.480 --> 03:17:05.731
NOODLES:
You did.

03:17:05.731 --> 03:17:07.566
You were terrific.

03:17:22.830 --> 03:17:26.209
“Age cannot wither her.”

03:17:26.209 --> 03:17:28.003
It's like the play
was written for you.

03:17:32.840 --> 03:17:34.593
What was the other reason?

03:17:35.636 --> 03:17:37.220
The other reason...

03:17:40.974 --> 03:17:44.520
...is to decide whether I should
go to a party tomorrow night.

03:17:52.027 --> 03:17:53.362
Party?

03:17:56.615 --> 03:17:58.158
Yeah, on Long Island.

03:18:00.661 --> 03:18:03.121
A Secretary Bailey.

03:18:07.751 --> 03:18:09.545
Do you know
Secretary Bailey?

03:18:11.921 --> 03:18:13.256
No.

03:18:15.050 --> 03:18:17.219
But I was
invited anyway.

03:18:26.061 --> 03:18:27.479
But if you don't
know each other,

03:18:27.479 --> 03:18:29.272
why were you invited?

03:18:29.272 --> 03:18:30.607
I don't know.

03:18:32.150 --> 03:18:34.944
I thought you might know why.

03:18:34.944 --> 03:18:36.904
Me?

03:18:36.904 --> 03:18:38.407
Why me?

03:18:44.120 --> 03:18:46.122
Because you know him.

03:18:46.122 --> 03:18:47.332
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

03:18:47.332 --> 03:18:48.542
Who is it?

03:18:48.542 --> 03:18:49.877
MAN:
It's me, Deborah, David--

03:18:49.877 --> 03:18:51.211
No, David!
Uh, d--

03:18:51.211 --> 03:18:52.546
Can I come in?

03:18:52.546 --> 03:18:54.423
No, no, no. You--
Just wait outside, David,

03:18:54.423 --> 03:18:55.591
I'll call you.

03:18:55.591 --> 03:18:57.885
DAVID:
Okay, I'll be right here.

03:19:00.220 --> 03:19:01.971
What does Secretary Bailey
want from me?

03:19:01.971 --> 03:19:03.973
You came here
to ask me that?

03:19:03.973 --> 03:19:05.392
Why did he send me
an invitation?

03:19:05.392 --> 03:19:07.102
I don't know, I don't know.
I don't know.

03:19:07.102 --> 03:19:08.437
I-- Why--?
Why should I--?

03:19:08.437 --> 03:19:10.146
Why should I know
about your invitation?

03:19:10.146 --> 03:19:11.732
I don't know anything.
I-- He--

03:19:11.732 --> 03:19:13.442
Uh, what-- What do you
want from me?

03:19:13.442 --> 03:19:16.027
Why did you come here? I know
nothing. I know nothing!

03:19:16.027 --> 03:19:18.988
Now you're
a lousy actress.

03:19:21.700 --> 03:19:24.244
Who is
Secretary Bailey?

03:19:33.086 --> 03:19:36.632
Secretary Bailey
is a rich businessman.

03:19:41.929 --> 03:19:44.222
He came to the United States

03:19:44.222 --> 03:19:45.515
as a starving immigrant

03:19:45.515 --> 03:19:47.142
and made a lot of money

03:19:47.142 --> 03:19:49.352
in San Francisco
and Los Angeles,

03:19:49.352 --> 03:19:51.354
where he's lived for 30 years.

03:19:51.354 --> 03:19:53.523
I know all that.
It's all in the papers.

03:19:53.523 --> 03:19:55.233
What else is there?

03:20:02.198 --> 03:20:04.827
He married a very wealthy woman.

03:20:06.244 --> 03:20:08.037
They had a child.

03:20:09.372 --> 03:20:11.040
She died
when the child was born.

03:20:12.668 --> 03:20:14.336
A few years ago,

03:20:14.336 --> 03:20:16.254
he went into politics.

03:20:16.254 --> 03:20:17.547
Moved here.

03:20:17.547 --> 03:20:19.048
That's all past history.

03:20:19.048 --> 03:20:21.551
I'm not talking about that.
I'm talking about now.

03:20:22.970 --> 03:20:25.430
Right now he's in trouble.

03:20:27.014 --> 03:20:28.350
Why can't you just tell me

03:20:28.350 --> 03:20:30.686
you've been living
with him all these years

03:20:30.686 --> 03:20:32.688
and that you're his lover?

03:20:41.237 --> 03:20:43.490
Age can wither me, Noodles.

03:20:47.870 --> 03:20:50.288
We're both getting old.

03:20:55.627 --> 03:20:59.046
All that we have left now
are our memories.

03:21:02.133 --> 03:21:05.220
If you go to that party
on Saturday night,

03:21:05.220 --> 03:21:07.014
you won't have those anymore.

03:21:09.224 --> 03:21:13.353
Tear up that invitation.

03:21:14.312 --> 03:21:17.024
There's an exit back this way.

03:21:18.274 --> 03:21:20.485
Noodles, go through it.

03:21:23.446 --> 03:21:25.407
Keep walking.

03:21:25.407 --> 03:21:27.409
Don't turn around.

03:21:29.160 --> 03:21:31.120
Please, Noodles.

03:21:31.120 --> 03:21:32.455
I'm begging you,

03:21:32.455 --> 03:21:34.374
please.

03:21:41.214 --> 03:21:43.926
Are you afraid that I'll
turn into a pillar of salt?

03:21:47.763 --> 03:21:51.016
If you go out
that door, yes.

03:22:09.034 --> 03:22:11.244
[♪♪♪]

03:22:49.616 --> 03:22:52.995
DEBORAH:
This is Secretary Bailey's son.

03:22:52.995 --> 03:22:56.331
His name's David,
just like yours.

03:22:56.331 --> 03:22:59.250
[♪♪♪]

03:24:46.608 --> 03:24:49.527
[ORCHESTRA PLAYING DANCE MUSIC]

03:24:51.988 --> 03:24:53.865
[INAUDIBLE]

03:25:48.377 --> 03:25:50.546
MAN:
Please, go in.

03:26:04.727 --> 03:26:06.646
What are
you waiting for?

03:26:10.525 --> 03:26:13.153
I don't understand,
Mr. Bailey.

03:26:39.721 --> 03:26:41.556
Sit down, Noodles.

03:26:45.977 --> 03:26:47.979
Make yourself comfortable.

03:27:05.955 --> 03:27:08.666
I'm glad you accepted
my invitation.

03:27:08.666 --> 03:27:11.336
Well,
I was curious.

03:27:13.880 --> 03:27:17.092
So many important people
in one place.

03:27:17.092 --> 03:27:20.262
MAX:
Yes. Well, the rats usually
desert a sinking ship.

03:27:21.554 --> 03:27:22.764
In my case,

03:27:22.764 --> 03:27:25.308
they appear to be
flocking onboard.

03:27:36.986 --> 03:27:38.988
Yeah, well, I read
about your troubles

03:27:38.988 --> 03:27:41.157
in the newspapers.

03:27:42.575 --> 03:27:44.577
A man in your position,

03:27:44.577 --> 03:27:47.163
with all your power
and all your privileges,

03:27:47.163 --> 03:27:51.251
has to assume a certain
amount of responsibility.

03:27:52.459 --> 03:27:54.629
A certain amount of risk.

03:28:02.011 --> 03:28:05.390
Why'd you ask me
to come here, Mr. Bailey?

03:28:08.226 --> 03:28:11.020
That invitation doesn't
mean a goddamn thing

03:28:11.020 --> 03:28:13.522
and you know it.

03:28:13.522 --> 03:28:17.235
All that counts is what
was in that suitcase.

03:28:18.527 --> 03:28:21.281
The money
and the contract.

03:28:23.616 --> 03:28:26.619
It didn't say who
the contract was on, though.

03:28:28.579 --> 03:28:31.082
Haven't you figured
that out yet?

03:28:32.541 --> 03:28:34.294
You, Mr. Bailey?

03:28:47.598 --> 03:28:51.311
I haven't had a gun in my hand
for many, many years.

03:28:53.313 --> 03:28:56.316
My eyes aren't too good,
even with my glasses.

03:28:56.316 --> 03:28:58.985
My hands shake.

03:29:01.654 --> 03:29:04.366
And I wouldn't
wanna miss, Mr. Bailey.

03:29:04.366 --> 03:29:05.908
Cut the bullshit,
Noodles.

03:29:07.285 --> 03:29:10.455
I'm already
a dead man.

03:29:10.455 --> 03:29:12.207
At least give me
the chance

03:29:12.207 --> 03:29:14.501
to settle the debt
that I owe to you.

03:29:16.127 --> 03:29:19.755
I'll never make it before
the investigating committee.

03:29:19.755 --> 03:29:21.132
They're scared to death

03:29:21.132 --> 03:29:23.385
I'll implicate
the whole bunch of them.

03:29:23.385 --> 03:29:25.678
They gotta get rid of me.

03:29:29.140 --> 03:29:31.851
Today is as good a day
as any.

03:29:34.187 --> 03:29:36.939
You do it, Noodles.

03:29:36.939 --> 03:29:40.402
You're the only person
I can accept it from.

03:29:47.450 --> 03:29:50.203
You see, I found out
where you were.

03:29:50.203 --> 03:29:53.498
I brought you
back here for this.

03:29:54.832 --> 03:29:57.877
To even the score
between you and me.

03:30:00.171 --> 03:30:03.007
You can get out
through there.

03:30:10.223 --> 03:30:12.392
It leads right down
to the street.

03:30:12.392 --> 03:30:15.895
Nobody will see you.

03:30:21.234 --> 03:30:23.528
I don't know what you're
talking about, Mr. Bailey.

03:30:23.528 --> 03:30:25.530
You don't owe me a thing.

03:30:33.955 --> 03:30:36.207
Your eyes were
too full of tears

03:30:36.207 --> 03:30:37.542
to see that
it wasn't me

03:30:37.542 --> 03:30:40.420
lying there burned up
on that street.

03:30:40.420 --> 03:30:42.964
It was somebody else.

03:30:42.964 --> 03:30:46.050
You were too shocked
to realize

03:30:46.050 --> 03:30:47.510
that the cops
were in on it too.

03:30:49.429 --> 03:30:52.390
That was a syndicate
operation, Noodles.

03:31:03.443 --> 03:31:05.528
You're crazy.

03:31:07.780 --> 03:31:09.698
You said that to me
once before

03:31:09.698 --> 03:31:12.201
a long time ago,

03:31:12.201 --> 03:31:14.162
but my mind
was never as clear

03:31:14.162 --> 03:31:16.247
as it was
at that moment.

03:31:16.247 --> 03:31:20.460
I took away your
whole life from you.

03:31:20.460 --> 03:31:22.378
I've been living
in your place.

03:31:24.255 --> 03:31:26.673
I took everything.

03:31:28.343 --> 03:31:30.052
I took your money.

03:31:31.387 --> 03:31:33.806
I took your girl.

03:31:33.806 --> 03:31:36.518
All I left for you
was 35 years of grief

03:31:36.518 --> 03:31:38.811
over having killed me.

03:31:40.480 --> 03:31:42.857
Now, why don't you
shoot?

03:31:47.778 --> 03:31:50.281
[♪♪♪]

03:32:47.088 --> 03:32:49.674
[INAUDIBLE]

03:33:17.535 --> 03:33:20.329
It's true I have
killed people, Mr. Bailey.

03:33:20.329 --> 03:33:22.415
Sometimes
to defend myself,

03:33:22.415 --> 03:33:24.292
sometimes for money.

03:33:25.376 --> 03:33:27.712
And many people
used to come to us:

03:33:27.712 --> 03:33:31.633
business partners, rivals,

03:33:31.633 --> 03:33:34.385
lovers.

03:33:34.385 --> 03:33:37.305
Some of the jobs we took
and some we didn't.

03:33:51.569 --> 03:33:54.821
Yours is one we would
never touch, Mr. Bailey.

03:33:54.821 --> 03:33:57.408
Is this your way
of getting revenge?

03:34:02.079 --> 03:34:04.457
No.

03:34:07.168 --> 03:34:09.671
It's just the way
I see things.

03:35:13.150 --> 03:35:15.611
It's 10:25.

03:35:17.363 --> 03:35:19.866
And I've got
nothing left to lose.

03:35:22.368 --> 03:35:24.245
When you've been
betrayed by a friend,

03:35:24.245 --> 03:35:25.830
you hit back.

03:35:31.252 --> 03:35:33.045
Do it.

03:35:55.610 --> 03:35:57.904
You see,
Mr. Secretary...

03:35:59.946 --> 03:36:02.575
...I have a story also.

03:36:02.575 --> 03:36:05.703
A little simpler
than yours.

03:36:06.746 --> 03:36:08.997
Many years ago,
I had a friend.

03:36:08.997 --> 03:36:11.208
A dear friend.

03:36:13.001 --> 03:36:16.213
I turned him in
to save his life.

03:36:16.213 --> 03:36:18.758
But he was killed.

03:36:20.050 --> 03:36:22.762
But he wanted it that way.

03:36:23.930 --> 03:36:26.390
It was a great friendship.

03:36:29.184 --> 03:36:31.186
Went bad for him.

03:36:31.186 --> 03:36:33.606
It went bad for me too.

03:36:37.693 --> 03:36:38.985
Good night, Mr. Bailey.

03:36:49.455 --> 03:36:52.291
I hope the investigation
turns out to be nothing.

03:36:54.669 --> 03:36:55.962
It would be a shame

03:36:55.962 --> 03:36:59.924
to see a lifetime
of work go to waste.

